definitions.definition: Having regular jurisdiction ; now only used in certain phrases .
Being part of the natural order of things; normal , customary , routine .
examples: On an ordinary day I wake up at nine o'clock, work for six hours, and then go to the gym.

definitions.definition: Having no special characteristics or function; everyday , common , mundane ; often deprecatory .
examples: I live a very ordinary life most of the time, but every year I spend a week in Antarctica.
He looked so ordinary , I never thought he'd be capable of murder.

main_definition: ( law , of a judge ) Having regular jurisdiction ; now only used in certain phrases .
secondary_definitions: Being part of the natural order of things; normal , customary , routine .
Having no special characteristics or function; everyday , common , mundane ; often deprecatory .
( Australia , New Zealand , colloquial , informal ) Bad or undesirable .
